Heat the oil in small saucepan over a medium heat. Add the red onion and cook for 2–3 minutes, or until it begins to soften. Add the red pepper, garlic, chilli flakes, tomatoes, tomato purée, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Add the prawns and cook for 5 minutes.Meanwhile, place the courgetti in a microwave and cook on high for 2 minutes. Leave to stand for 1 minute before serving with the sauce.